 at Diocesan Boys' School]]\n[[Category:People from Maui]]\n[[Category:People from Oahu]]\n[[Category:People of the Xinhai Revolution]]\n[[Category:People who died in office]]\n[[Category:Philosophers from Guangdong]]\n[[Category:Physicians from Guangdong]]\n[[Category:Political party founders]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Zhongshan]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Republic of China]]\n[[Category:Queen's College, Hong Kong alumni]]\n[[Category:Republic of China (1912\u20131949)]]\n[[Category:Republic of China politicians from Guangdong]]\n[[Category:Sun Yat-sen family]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese physicians]]\n[[Category:Tongmenghui members]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Chinese physician, politician and revolutionary}}\n{{Redirect|Sun Wen|the female Chinese footballer|Sun Wen (footballer)}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Sun (surname)|Sun]]}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific_prefix    = \n| name                = Sun Yat-sen\n| native_name         = {{nobold|{{lang|zh-hant|\u5b6b\u4e2d\u5c71 / \u5b6b\u9038\u4ed9}}}}<br />{{small|{{small|{{nobold|[[#Names|''other names'']]}}}}}}\n| native_name_lang    = zh\n| honorific_suffix    = \n| image               = \u5b59\u4e2d\u5c71\u8096\u50cf.jpg\n| caption             = Sun Yat-Sen in the 1910s\n| office              = [[List of Presidents of the Republic of China|Provisional President of the Republic of China]]\n| term_start          = 1 January 1912\n| term_end            = 10 March 1912\n| vicepresident       = [[Li Yuanhong]]\n| predecessor         = [[Puyi]] ([[Emperor of China]])\n| successor           = [[Yuan Shikai]]\n| office2             = [[List of leaders of the Kuomintang|Premier]] of the [[Kuomintang]]\n| predecessor2        = Position established\n| successor2          = [[Zhang Renjie]] (as chairman)\n| term_start2         = 10 October 1919\n| term_end2           = 12 March 1925\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date|df=y|1866|11|12}}\n| birth_place         = [[Cuiheng]], [[